content: Ok, so here are our definitions of natural and supernatural: 1) "natural" refers to phenomena that exist or occur in the physical universe and are subject to its laws and processes, including those that can be observed, studied, and explained through empirical evidence and scientific inquiry." 2) "Broadly speaking, the term "supernatural" refers to phenomena or entities that are believed to exist beyond the scope of natural laws or the physical world, and are typically attributed to some sort of higher power, deity, or divine force. This can include concepts such as gods, angels, demons, spirits, and other supernatural beings or forces that are often associated with religious or spiritual belief systems."
